x(t+h)=x(t)+hx'(t)+Kh^2
x'(t)\approx\frac{1}{h}(x(t+h)-x(t))
L = x'(t)
\phi(h) = \frac{1}{h}(x(t+h)-x(t))
L = \phi(h)+hK+O(h^{2})
2L = 2\phi(\frac{h}{2})+2K\frac{h}{2}+O(h^{2})
L= 2\phi(\frac{h}{2})-\phi(h)+O(h^{2})
2\phi(\frac{h}{2})-\phi(h) = f(t+\frac{1}{2} h,x(t)+\frac{1}{2} hf(t,x(t)))
